## Entry Options for New Students

### Option A: Complete Beginner (Ages 11-13)

Students with no coding experience start at Term 1. The accelerated pace is appropriate for their age—they'll cover Year 1 concepts more quickly in Terms 1-2 before moving to advanced material.

### Option B: Year 1 Graduate

Students who completed the Ages 9-10 curriculum can:
- **Fast track:** Take a placement test and potentially skip to Term 3 or 4
- **Standard path:** Start at Term 1 for reinforcement and quickly advance

### Option C: Some Experience

Students with prior coding experience take a placement assessment to determine the best starting point.

